<CENTER><FONT face=Sylfaen,georgia size=6 color=white>9/11 VIGILANTES</FONT></CENTER><P align=justify><FONT face=arial COLOR=aqua><A HREF="http://www.fdungan.com/vigilantes.htm"><IMG ALIGN=left SRC=vigilantes.gif ALT="9/11 Vigilantes by Fred Dungan" BORDER=2"></A>Read the hard-hitting book they wouldn't publish for fear it might incite people to riot. <i><A href="http://www.fdungan.com/vigilantes.htm"></FONT><FONT FACE=arial COLOR=white>9/11 Vigilantes</i></A></FONT><FONT face=arial COLOR=aqua> tells the action-packed story of the reaction of ordinary Americans to the senseless slaughter on September 11, 2001.&nbsp; Although fiction, much of <i><A href="http://www.fdungan.com/vigilantes.htm"></FONT><FONT FACE=arial COLOR=white>9/11 Vigilantes</i></A></FONT><FONT face=arial COLOR=aqua> is based on actual post 9/11 events.&nbsp; The story is told by Ryan, a teenager in a small western resort town whose father is the local Sheriff, but this definitely isn't Opie in Mayberry.&nbsp; Following 9/11, the concerned citizens of Hermosa are up in arms about the failure of law enforcement to stop illegal immigration and protect them from terrorists.&nbsp; Street justice&mdash;the kind dispensed by vigilantes and militias&mdash;is preferable to no justice whatsoever.  Ride with Ryan Romero and his posse as they pursue al-Qaeda terrorists across the vast expanse of the High Desert.</FONT><BR><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="line001.gif" WIDTH="00537" HEIGHT="00020" ALT=""></CENTER><DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
